<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF8FFD9A5CDFA2F1C2DF9D1" blockId="8.[136,530,1526,1553]" box="[136,530,1526,1553]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFF8FFD9A5CDFA2F1C2DF9D1" box="[136,530,1526,1553]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="4">
2. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF8FFD9A5E1FA2F1C31F9D1" authority="Chamisso (1832: 252)" authorityName="Chamisso" authorityPageNumber="252" authorityYear="1832" box="[164,526,1526,1553]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Bouchea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A5E1FA2F1F34F9D1" bold="true" box="[164,267,1526,1553]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bouchea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF8FFD9A457FA2F1C31F9D1" author="Chamisso, L. K. A." box="[274,526,1526,1553]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="105 - 723" refId="ref34315" refString="Chamisso, L. K. A. (1832) Verbenaceae. Linnaea 7: 105 - 723." type="journal article" year="1832">Chamisso (1832: 252)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF8FFD9A5CDF9E71A5FF8CC" blockId="8.[136,1452,1598,1985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Subshrubs, monoecious, branches without prickles, not aromatic. Leaves petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences terminal, simple, racemes spiciform, multiflowered, rachis elongated; bracts membranaceous, green, bracteoles 2 per flower. Flowers pedicellate; calyx cylindrical-tubular, shorter than the corolla, membranaceous, green, 5-toothed, not accrescent in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed; stamens 4, included, didynamous, superior pair without connective appendages, thecae parallel or slightly divergent; ovary 1-carpelate, 2-loculate, ovules 1 per locule, stigma oblique. Fruit a schizocarp, with 2 cluses, brown, external surface striate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFF8FFD9A5F8F8CF1F56F801" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF8FFD9A5F8F8CF1F56F801" blockId="8.[136,1452,1598,1985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF8FFD9A5F8F8CF1F20F8F0" authorityName="Chamisso" authorityYear="1832" box="[189,287,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Bouchea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A5F8F8CF1F20F8F0" box="[189,287,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bouchea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF8FFD9A4BDF8CE1D7DF8F0" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[504,834,1814,1841]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Duranteae">
Duranteae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF8FFD9A73FF8CF1D05F8F0" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[634,826,1814,1840]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A785F8CE1CC6F8F0" box="[704,761,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and presents 13 species distributed from South 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF8FFD9A01AF8CF1EF4F894" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">United States</collectingCountry>
to North 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF8FFD9A472F8E31F99F894" box="[311,422,1850,1876]" name="Argentina" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF8FFD9A4F3F8E31CEDF894" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Moroni, P." box="[438,722,1850,1876]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="02591" refId="ref36513" refString="O'Leary, N. &amp; Moroni, P. (2019) A contribution towards resolving the nomenclature of Citharexylum (Verbenaceae). II. Remarks on implicit typifications and lectotypification of names linked to Mesoamerican taxa. Nordic Journal of Botany 37: e 02591. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / njb. 02591" type="journal article" year="2019">Moroni &amp; O’Leary 2019</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A607F8E21DDEF894" box="[834,993,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al. in press.</emphasis>
). The genus is characterized by terminal inflorescences, spiciform, bracteolates, pedicellate flowers, and four fertile stamens (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF8FFD9A11CF8871B40F8B8" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Moroni, P." box="[1113,1407,1886,1912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="02591" refId="ref36513" refString="O'Leary, N. &amp; Moroni, P. (2019) A contribution towards resolving the nomenclature of Citharexylum (Verbenaceae). II. Remarks on implicit typifications and lectotypification of names linked to Mesoamerican taxa. Nordic Journal of Botany 37: e 02591. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / njb. 02591" type="journal article" year="2019">Moroni &amp; O’Leary 2019</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFF8FFD9A5CDF85B1EF0F85C" box="[136,207,1922,1948]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, there are three species, of which two are endemic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF8FFD9A66FF85B1A64F85D" author="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N." box="[810,1115,1922,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref36147" refString="Moroni, P. &amp; O'Leary, N. (2020 b) Bouchea in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15132 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Moroni &amp; O’Leary 2020b</bibRefCitation>
). One species is recorded for 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFF8FFD9A5CDF87F1F59F801" box="[136,358,1958,1985]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Espírito Santo state</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
